Legs (
Fig. 7
). Structure and chaetotaxy typical for the genus. Tarsi II–IV subdivided into basitarsus and telotarsus by complete peripodomeric fissure. All setae simple.

Legs (
Fig. 10
). Structure and chaetotaxy as for female, except setae d and pl on genu and tibia I robust, short. Setae av on genu, tibia and tarsus II robust. Tarsi II–IV subdivided into basitarsus and telotarsus by complete peripodomeric fissure. All leg setae smooth.

Dorsal idiosoma (
Fig. 11
). Length 550–577 µm, width 460–475 µm (n = 10 ). Dorsal shield subcircular, smooth, marginal shield absent. Posterior end of idiosoma undulate. Dorsal setae numerous, robust, ca 57 µm long. Between the setae ca 6 pairs of dorsal lyrifissures ( id ). Submarginal setae simple, ca 19 µm. Marginal setae very numerous, short, hook-like, slightly ventral in position.
